methods.descriptorForName:
Convenience method to convert from a scoped variable name to Flight.FlightDescriptor

:param name: (java.lang.String) - the scoped variable name to convert
:return: (org.apache.arrow.flight.impl.Flight.FlightDescriptor) the flight descriptor this descriptor represents
methods.descriptorToTicket:
Convenience method to convert from a Flight.Descriptor to a Flight.Ticket.

:param descriptor: (org.apache.arrow.flight.impl.Flight.FlightDescriptor) - the descriptor to convert
:param logId: (java.lang.String) - an end-user friendly identification of the ticket should an error occur
:return: (org.apache.arrow.flight.impl.Flight.Ticket) a flight ticket that represents the descriptor
methods.flightInfoFor:
Retrieve a FlightInfo for a given FlightDescriptor.

:param session: io.deephaven.grpc_api.session.SessionState
:param descriptor: org.apache.arrow.flight.impl.Flight.FlightDescriptor
:param logId: java.lang.String
:return: (io.deephaven.grpc_api.session.SessionState.ExportObject<org.apache.arrow.flight.impl.Flight.FlightInfo>) a FlightInfo describing this flight
methods.flightTicketForName:
Convenience method to convert from a scoped variable name to Flight.Ticket

:param name: (java.lang.String) - the scoped variable name to convert
:return: (org.apache.arrow.flight.impl.Flight.Ticket) the flight ticket this descriptor represents
methods.forAllFlightInfo:
This invokes the provided visitor for each valid flight descriptor this ticket resolver exposes via flight.

:param session: (io.deephaven.grpc_api.session.SessionState) - optional session that the resolver can use to filter which flights a visitor sees
:param visitor: (java.util.function.Consumer<org.apache.arrow.flight.impl.Flight.FlightInfo>) - the callback to invoke per descriptor path
methods.getLogNameFor:
Create a human readable string to identify this ticket.

:param ticket: (java.nio.ByteBuffer) - the ticket to parse
:param logId: (java.lang.String) - an end-user friendly identification of the ticket should an error occur
:return: (java.lang.String) a string that is good for log/error messages
